  "market_context": "E-mini S&P 500 on the 1-hour, price was in a downtrend with a defined low near 4141 and a range high near 4186. The analyst expected the downtrend low to be swept as sellside liquidity before a retest setup formed.",
  "key_observation": "Price aggressively drove below the old low and then aggressively pushed back inside the range, with the old low subsequently supporting price — a textbook box setup deviation on the sellside in a downtrend context.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Identified the range using the bodies, marking the range low around 4141 and range high around 4186 on the 1-hour ES chart.",
    "Noted the downtrend context and anticipated the low would be raided (sellside liquidity sweep).",
    "Observed an aggressive move down through the low followed by an aggressive move right back inside the range — the deviation from the range.",
    "Marked the deviation zone and waited for a retest of the old low, expecting it to now support price.",
    "Projected price to travel from the retest of the deviation back toward the opposite side of the range (the highs) as the target."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
  "lessons": "The box setup is not limited to ranges in isolation — in a downtrend, an aggressive sweep of the low followed by an aggressive reclaim turns the old low into support, offering a high-probability long retest toward the opposite side of the range.",
